{"TopicId":200270,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Kerbin Comm Network in Career mode","CreatedByName":"alphaprior","CreatedById":185480,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T14:46:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"alphaprior","CreatedById":185480,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T14:46:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShould I create a Comm Network around Kerbin?\u003Cbr\u003E\nSince I can see but not use other launch sites and they work as relays meaning I have signal almost all around Kerbin. Although I would like to disable them but there is no such option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd what about geostationary triangle orbit? I\u0027ve seen Scott Manley\u0027s video but I cannot understand when and how he sets the sats in the different positions apart.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI understand that I have to put my ship carrying all 3 sats in geostationary orbit as in video 2868.75K then I don\u0027t understand what to do with 2nd and 3d sat. I have to reduce periapsis to 1227? And circularize back? when?\u003Cbr\u003E\nAccording to KSP wiki for other planets and sun I need to have at least 1 equatorial and 1 polar orbit. Should I do this in Kerbin also?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-02-11T14:47:16Z\u0022 title=\u002202/11/2021 02:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 11, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by alphaprior\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T15:04:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613054796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185480\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alphaprior\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, alphaprior said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlthough I would like to disable them but there is no such option\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Kerbal-Space-Program-2021-02-11-15-57-39\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002276.13\u0022 height=\u0022437\u0022 width=\u0022574\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/rtpDcrH/Kerbal-Space-Program-2021-02-11-15-57-39.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613054796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185480\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alphaprior\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, alphaprior said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd what about geostationary triangle orbit? I\u0027ve seen Scott Manley\u0027s video but I cannot understand when and how he sets the sats in the different positions apart.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t have to be a geostationary obit, no extra benefits from that. In general, how to set up:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Rx5gKxX4q-Y?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613054796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185480\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alphaprior\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, alphaprior said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have to reduce periapsis to 1227? And circularize back? when?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShould be covered in that video as well, iirc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613054796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185480\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alphaprior\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, alphaprior said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAccording to KSP wiki for other planets and sun I need to have at least 1 equatorial and 1 polar orbit. Should I do this in Kerbin also?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI usually follow this guide here (more or less):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T15:07:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s up to you really. 3 sats separated equally provide connection 99% of time regardless of other spacecraft position in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI put two, on opposite sides of the orbit, and one polar. Their position will change a bit anyway. But I don\u0027t really go for geostationary, even though I try to hit that 2868km, mine are geosynchronous. With orbital period equal to rotation of the body.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you will need more commsats once you travel further than Kerbin. If you land on side of Duna that\u0027s not visible from Kerbin, it\u0027s better to have a sat in orbit there so you don\u0027t lose connection every few hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-02-11T15:09:07Z\u0022 title=\u002202/11/2021 03:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 11, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by The Aziz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alphaprior","CreatedById":185480,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T15:43:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613055879\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t have to be a geostationary obit, no extra benefits from that. In general, how to set up:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShould be covered in that video as well, iirc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI usually follow this guide here (more or less):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanx! Setting worked stations did not dissapear but at least they don\u0027t have a signal anymore.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd video is very similar to Scott Manley\u0027s tutorial but I got it. First I get into an elliptical orbit 2868-1227 then I release a sat at AP in every orbit, and raise PE to 2868.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI want to use geostationary orbit because why not? I could set any orbit but this is cool and realistic. Maybe in KSP2 will be essential untill then...\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924434\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613056051\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s up to you really. 3 sats separated equally provide connection 99% of time regardless of other spacecraft position in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI put two, on opposite sides of the orbit, and one polar. Their position will change a bit anyway. But I don\u0027t really go for geostationary, even though I try to hit that 2868km, mine are geosynchronous. With orbital period equal to rotation of the body.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you will need more commsats once you travel further than Kerbin. If you land on side of Duna that\u0027s not visible from Kerbin, it\u0027s better to have a sat in orbit there so you don\u0027t lose connection every few hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is my 2nd career game so I intend to carry at least 3 sats on every planetary mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T16:36:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve found the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EResonant Orbit Calculator\u003C/a\u003E to be wonderful for setting up 3x comsats in a single launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T16:53:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...which is also available in game:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5391002092\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/177833-19x-ksp-resonant-orbit-calculator/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T16:57:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924508\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613062386\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...which is also available in game:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9237584802\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/177833-19x-ksp-resonant-orbit-calculator/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup, but the web version works for stock games and even for consoles \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T18:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613062654\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand even for consoles\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYepp \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924454\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221613058194\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185480\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alphaprior\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, alphaprior said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst I get into an elliptical orbit 2868-1227 then I release a sat at AP in every orbit, and raise PE to 2868.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI usually start with a circular orbit, deploy a relay satellite, and immediately raise the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E as per the calculation. Switch to the just deployed satellite and fine tune the orbital period as precise as possible, the time is important here, doesn\u0027t matter is the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is a bit off from what is planned. Next, switching back to the carrier rocket, warp to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, circularize, then deploy the next satellite.\u00A0 And so forth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-02-11T18:35:59Z\u0022 title=\u002202/11/2021 06:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 11, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}